{{Refimprove|date=February 2009}} {{Infobox song contest entry | song = {{flagicon|Malta}} "Angel" | image = | caption = | year = 2005 | country = Malta | artist = [[Chiara Siracusa|Chiara]] | as = | with = | language = English | languages = | composer = [[Chiara Siracusa]] | lyricist = [[Chiara Siracusa]] | place = 2nd | points = 192 | place_semi = | points_semi = | lyrics = [http://www.diggiloo.net/?2005mt from Diggiloo Thrush] | prev = On Again... Off Again | prev_link = On Again... Off Again | next = I Do | next_link = I Do (Fabrizio Faniello song) }} '''"Angel"''' was the [[Malta|Maltese]] entry in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2005]], performed in [[English language|English]] by [[Chiara Siracusa|Chiara]].
In contrast to the up-tempo styles dominating the Contest, the song is a solo love ballad. Chiara sings to her lover that, no matter what, she will be "your angel". The chorus culminates with the line "I'm always here for you".
In keeping with the lyrical simplicity of the song, Chiara performed solo onstage with a simple musical score backing her.
As Malta had finished the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2004|2004 Contest]] in the top 12, the song was pre-qualified for the final. Here, it was performed third, following the [[United Kingdom]]'s [[Javine Hylton|Javine]] with "[[Touch My Fire]]" and preceding [[Romania]]'s [[Luminiţa Anghel]] & [[Sistem]] with "[[Let Me Try (Luminiţa Anghel and Sistem song)|Let Me Try]]". At the close of voting, it had received 192 points placing 2nd in a field of 24 and pre-qualifying Malta for the final at the next Contest. In the voting, Malta received only one 12-point set, from Russia, a low number for a Eurovision runner-up.
The result was also Malta's best in Contest history, equalling [[Ira Losco]]'s second place with "[[7th Wonder]]" but exceeding that song's score of 164 points (and indeed Chiara's own score of 165 with "[[The One That I Love]]"). "Angel" managed to peak at #95 on the German Singles Chart Top 100.
The song appeared as a "favourite" on the CD and DVD sets produced to commemorate the [[Congratulations (Eurovision)|Congratulations]] special in late 2005.
It was succeeded as [[Malta in the Eurovision Song Contest|Maltese representative]] at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2006|2006 Contest]] by [[Fabrizio Faniello]] with "[[I Do (Fabrizio Faniello song)|I Do]]".
==Covers== The song has gained popularity in many countries. The South African singer [[Tobi Jooste]] recorded the song as "Engel"[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4gNL73q6SwE] in [[Afrikaans language]] on his album ''Onthou Jy''.<ref>[http://ogae.esckaz.com/south_africa_covers.htm OGAE Rest of the World presents South African Eurovision Covers]</ref>
