{{Infobox_Diplomatic_Mission | name = Embassy of Ireland, Bern [[Image:Coat_of_arms_of_Ireland.svg|100px]] | address = Kirchenfeldstrasse 68, CH-3000 Berne 6, Switzerland | location = [[Bern]] | coordinates = {{coord|46.940223|N|7.455509|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | ambassador = Breifne O'Reilly | website = [https://www.dfa.ie/irish-embassy/switzerland/ Irish Embassy, Switzerland] }}
The '''Embassy of Ireland''' in [[Switzerland]] ({{lang-de|Botschaft von Irland, Schweiz}}) is the [[diplomatic mission]] of [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]] to [[Switzerland]]. It is located in the Swiss city of [[Bern]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dfa.ie/irish-embassy/switzerland/about-us/the-embassy/|title=The Embassy - Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade|website=www.dfa.ie|language=en|access-date=2018-07-25}}</ref>
The embassy is also represented in Switzerland by [[Consul (representative)|Honorary Consuls]] in [[Zurich]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dfa.ie/irish-embassy/switzerland/about-us/honorary-consulate-zurich/|title=Honorary Consulate of Ireland, Zurich - Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade|website=www.dfa.ie|language=en|access-date=2018-07-25}}</ref>
The current Irish Ambassador to Switzerland is Breifne O'Reilly.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dfa.ie/irish-embassy/switzerland/about-us/ambassador/|title=Ambassador - Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade|website=www.dfa.ie|language=en|access-date=2018-07-25}}</ref>
The Embassy of Ireland in Bern is also accredited on a non-residential basis to both [[Liechtenstein]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dfa.ie/irish-embassy/switzerland/about-us/ireland-in-liechtenstein/|title=Ireland in Liechtenstein - Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade|website=www.dfa.ie|language=en|access-date=2018-07-25}}</ref> and [[Algeria]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dfa.ie/irish-embassy/switzerland/about-us/ireland-in-algeria/|title=Ireland in Algeria - Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade|website=www.dfa.ie|language=en|access-date=2018-07-25}}</ref>.
