'''Kiev Interbank Offer Rate''' ('''KIBOR''') is a daily indicative rate based on the [[interest rates]] at which banks offer to lend unsecured funds to other banks on the [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] [[money market]] (or interbank market). KIBOR is the opposite of the [[Kiev Interbank Bid Rate]] (KIBID).

KIBOR is currently calculated for such [[currencies]] as: Ukrainian Hryvnia (UAH) and [[US Dollar]] (USD).

