{{third-party|date=June 2014}}
'''Naftalan''' is a [[naphthalene]] [[spa resort]] and [[skin conditions]] treatment and rehabilitation hospital in [[Ivanić-Grad]] in [[Zagreb County]], [[Croatia]]. It is located {{convert|27|km|abbr=on}} away from the city center of the country's capital [[Zagreb]], a 20-minute drive on the [[A3 (Croatia)|A3]] freeway. The hospital was opened in 1989 and sports 111 beds in rooms of up to three patients. Various amenities, such as a [[café]], a [[bowling]] alley, and [[Team handball|handball]], [[soccer|football]] and [[tennis]] courts, are available to patients.<ref name=naf_home>{{cite web|url=http://www.naftalan.hr/index.php/en/|title=Naftalan (Homepage) |work=Naftalan|accessdate=2009-03-19}}</ref> The hospital is aimed at treating patients with [[psoriasis]], [[atopic dermatitis|atopic]] and [[contact dermatitis]], and [[scleroderma]].<ref name=naf_skin>{{cite web |url=http://www.naftalan.hr/en/lijecenje/indikacije |title=Indications |work=Naftalan.hr |accessdate=2013-01-04}}</ref> Naftalan is a member of the [[European Spas Association]] (ESPA).<ref name=zg_espa>{{cite web |url=http://www.zagreb-touristinfo.hr/?id=159&solo=59&l=e |title=Naftalan Spa Joins the Elite European Society |date=April 2007 |work=[[Zagreb County|Zagreb Tourist Board]] |accessdate=2009-03-19}}</ref>

