{{Infobox mountain | name = Piz Gannaretsch | photo = File:PizGannaretschFromSE.jpg | photo_caption = Piz Gannaretsch from [[Lai da Sontga Maria]] | elevation_m = 3040 | elevation_ref = | prominence_m = 934 | prominence_ref = <ref>Retrieved from the [[Swisstopo]] topographic maps. The key col is the [[Gotthard Pass]] (2,106 m).</ref> | parent_peak = [[Finsteraarhorn]] | listing = [[List of mountains of the Alps above 3000 m|Alpine mountains above 3000 m]] | map = Switzerland | map_caption = Location in Switzerland | location = [[Graubünden]], [[Switzerland]] | range = [[Lepontine Alps]] | coordinates = {{coord|46|36|43.3|N|8|47|11.2|E|type:mountain_region:CH_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | range_coordinates = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }}
'''Piz Gannaretsch''' is a [[mountain]] in the [[Lepontine Alps]], overlooking [[Sedrun]] in [[Graubünden]]. At 3,040 metres above sea level, its summit is the highest point of the range lying between [[St Gotthard Pass]] and [[Lukmanier Pass]]. The massif of Piz Gannaretsch separates the valleys of [[Lake Nalps]] (west) and [[Lake Sontga Maria]] (east).
A glacier named ''Glatscher da Gannaretsch'' lies over the north-western flanks of Piz Gannaretsch.
